<sn><md>### Isobar{.text-center}

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-lg-7
&gt; A line on a map connecting places of `equal air pressure` is called ++isobar++.

* The `spacing of the isobars` indicates the amount of pressure change occuring over a given distance and it is expressed as the pressure gradient.
* `closely spaced isobar` lines indicate a bigger and steep pressure gradient over short distance and ++strong winds++.
* Whereas,`widely spaced isobars` indicate a small pressure gradient over big distance and ++gentle winds++.
* PGF drives wind at `90 angle` with the isobar line from `the higher pressure region to the lower pressure region` area,hence the start bowling ++perpendicular to isobars++.
:::

